        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Firefox Version 36'); ?>
        <p><strong>Firefox 36.0</strong> was released for desktop on 24 February 2015, bringing full HTTP/2 support and other smaller improvements and fixes. It was also released for <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Android', 'OS'); ?> three days later, adding support for the tablet user interface.</p>
        <p>Firefox 36.0.1 was released for desktop on 5 March 2015, and the next day for Android, fixing various issues.</p>
        <p>Firefox 36.0.2 was released for [Android] only on 16 March 2015, fixing a startup crash on HTC One M8 devices (Verizon) with Android 5.0.1 and some potential crashes with Flash videos.</p>
        <p>Firefox 36.0.3 was released on 20 March 2015; soon after that, Version 36.0.4 was released on 21 March 2015, for desktop and Android, fixing security issues disclosed at HP Zero Day Initiative's Pwn2Own contest.</p>
